				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\theta $$\end{document} cross-section dependence of the Mott events, allows a cross-check of the muon polarisation at the Mott positron energy.
Positron momentum and angular resolutions: positron momentum and angular resolutions are extracted using double-turn track events. The double-turn track is divided in two independent tracks, the two tracks are propagated towards the target and the difference between the relevant observable (i.e. the pe+\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
