				\begin{document}$$\theta _\mathrm {e}^{+}$$\end{document} variable) is computed.As final remarks it should be noted that the high Mott positron rate enables for a fast calibration, the method does not require a dedicated target (i.e. the Mott target is the MEG II muon stopping target) and does not need additional beam infrastructures.

