In the past decades, timing detectors based on scintillation counters with PMT read-out have been built and operated successfully. The best achievements with this technique gave time resolutions slightly better than 50 ps for a minimum ionising particle (e.g. [111, 112]). One of them was the MEG timing counter consisting of 30 scintillator bars (BC-404 with 80 ×\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
