The MEG LXe photon detector, shown in Fig. 56, was one of the world’s largest detectors based on LXe scintillation light with 900 l of LXe surrounded by 846 PMTs submerged in liquid to detect the scintillation light in the VUV range (λ=(175±5)nm\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
