				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\sigma _{t_{\mathrm {\gamma }}}\simeq {50}\hbox { ps}$$\end{document} assuming an electronic noise level up to 1 mV. The main improvements come from the better time of flight estimate, deriving from the better position reconstruction, and higher photon statistics. Since parameters such as the rise time of the waveform and the noise components may not be correctly considered in the simulation, the time resolution in the worse case might still be at the MEG level, hence a conservative estimation is σtγ∼\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
