Figure 81 shows a schematic view of the RDC detector: 12 plastic scintillator bars in the front detect the timing of the positrons, and 76 LYSO crystals behind are the calorimeter for energy measurement. In order to distinguish RMD positrons from Michel ones, both the PS and the LYSO calorimeter are finely segmented. Because the background rate is larger close to the beam axis, the width of the PS in the central region is 1 cm while it is 2 cm at the outer part. The size of each LYSO crystal is 2×2×2cm3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
